{"obs_mpfbfpf4_e1a176a6409b":{"observation":{"concepts":["AgentMemory setup","MCP configuration","agy proxy","knowledge graph extraction"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Updated environment variables in /Users/zasuo/.agentmemory/.env","Installed Antigravity MCP configuration to /Users/zasuo/.gemini/antigravity/mcp_config.json","Updated instructions in /Users/zasuo/.gemini/GEMINI.md from custom AGENTMEMORY.md","Copied skills to /Users/zasuo/.gemini/antigravity/skills","Started healthy AgentMemory instance at http://localhost:3111 and agy proxy at http://127.0.0.1:3129","AgentMemory viewer is available at http://localhost:3113"],"files":["/Users/zasuo/.agentmemory/.env","/Users/zasuo/.gemini/antigravity/mcp_config.json","/Users/zasuo/.gemini/GEMINI.md"],"id":"obs_mpfbfpf4_e1a176a6409b","importance":7,"narrative":"The Antigravity AgentMemory setup was initialized and verified successfully using the setup script. Key environment configurations, instructions, and skills were updated, and the local agy proxy along with the AgentMemory server were confirmed healthy. This establishes a structured memory foundation for the agent's context injection and knowledge graph extraction.","sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","subtitle":"Executed setup.sh using RTK bash command","timestamp":"2026-05-21T09:56:09.677Z","title":"Initialize AgentMemory setup with antigravity client","type":"command_run"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mpfbhlox_231afe8b309b":{"observation":{"concepts":["AgentMemory setup","MCP configuration","agy proxy","semantic memory","knowledge graph extraction"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Executed setup command: rtk bash setup.sh --client antigravity --skip-doctor --drop-stale-index","Updated environment variables configuration in /Users/zasuo/.agentmemory/.env","Verified agy OpenAI-compatible proxy is healthy at http://127.0.0.1:3129","Updated Antigravity MCP config at /Users/zasuo/.gemini/antigravity/mcp_config.json","Updated AgentMemory instructions in /Users/zasuo/.gemini/GEMINI.md from /Users/zasuo/AI-Tool/ag-agentmemory/custom/instructions/AGENTMEMORY.md","Copied AgentMemory skills from /Users/zasuo/AI-Tool/ag-agentmemory/custom/skills to /Users/zasuo/.gemini/antigravity/skills","Started AgentMemory service v0.9.21 successfully at http://localhost:3111 with Viewer at http://localhost:3113","Verified AgentMemory health with active flags: Knowledge graph extraction, Memory consolidation, LLM-powered observation compression, and In-conversation context injection"],"files":["/Users/zasuo/.agentmemory/.env","/Users/zasuo/.gemini/antigravity/mcp_config.json","/Users/zasuo/.gemini/GEMINI.md","/Users/zasuo/AI-Tool/ag-agentmemory/custom/instructions/AGENTMEMORY.md"],"id":"obs_mpfbhlox_231afe8b309b","importance":7,"narrative":"The AgentMemory setup script was executed successfully for the 'antigravity' client, configuring local environment variables, MCP settings, markdown rules, and copying skills. It launched the AgentMemory service along with the agy OpenAI-compatible proxy, and verified the configuration is healthy and connected. This establishes a durable semantic memory and knowledge graph extraction pipeline for subsequent AI agent operations.","sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","subtitle":"Configure and start AgentMemory service with agy proxy for Antigravity client","timestamp":"2026-05-21T09:57:38.160Z","title":"Run Antigravity AgentMemory setup script","type":"command_run"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mpfbpbe5_390f10393648":{"observation":{"concepts":["AgentMemory environment","MCP configuration","OpenAI proxy setup"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Updated environment configuration in /Users/zasuo/.agentmemory/.env","Established agy OpenAI proxy at http://127.0.0.1:3129","Installed Antigravity MCP config to /Users/zasuo/.gemini/antigravity/mcp_config.json","Installed AgentMemory rules to /Users/zasuo/.gemini/GEMINI.md","Copied skills directory to /Users/zasuo/.gemini/antigravity/skills","Started AgentMemory instance at http://localhost:3111 and web viewer at http://localhost:3113"],"files":["/Users/zasuo/.agentmemory/.env","/Users/zasuo/.gemini/antigravity/mcp_config.json","/Users/zasuo/.gemini/GEMINI.md"],"id":"obs_mpfbpbe5_390f10393648","importance":6,"narrative":"Script setup.sh ńĎ√£ ho√†n th√†nh viŠĽác thiŠļŅt lŠļ≠p m√īi tr∆įŠĽĚng l√†m viŠĽác cho client antigravity th√†nh c√īng. Qu√° tr√¨nh n√†y cŠļ•u h√¨nh ńĎŠļßy ńĎŠĽß proxy OpenAI t∆į∆°ng th√≠ch, cŠļ≠p nhŠļ≠t luŠļ≠t AgentMemory c√Ļng c√°c tŠĽáp kŠĽĻ nńÉng bŠĽē trŠĽ£, ńĎŠĽďng thŠĽĚi khŠĽüi ńĎŠĽông th√†nh c√īng dŠĽčch vŠĽ• AgentMemory gi√ļp l∆įu trŠĽĮ v√† ńĎŠĽďng bŠĽô ngŠĽĮ cŠļ£nh hiŠĽáu quŠļ£.","sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","subtitle":"rtk bash setup.sh --client antigravity --skip-doctor --drop-stale-index","timestamp":"2026-05-21T10:03:38.058Z","title":"Setup AgentMemory and MCP tools for antigravity client","type":"command_run"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mpfbpp1x_8c25bdf141cb":{"observation":{"concepts":["RTK command execution","shell delay execution"],"confidence":0.9,"facts":["The bash command 'rtk sleep 8' was executed.","The action was recorded at timestamp 2026-05-21T10:03:55.760Z."],"files":[],"id":"obs_mpfbpp1x_8c25bdf141cb","importance":4,"narrative":"The agent executed a sleep command for 8 seconds using the RTK wrapper in the shell environment. This introduces a controlled delay, likely during an orchestration or waiting step.","sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","subtitle":"Bash tool execution under RTK environment","timestamp":"2026-05-21T10:03:55.760Z","title":"Execution of rtk sleep 8 command","type":"command_run"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mpfbpuvu_0806c338213f":{"observation":{"concepts":["Health check","Microservices health","Performance bottleneck","Memory compression metrics"],"confidence":1,"facts":["DŠĽčch vŠĽ• AgentMemory ńĎang hoŠļ°t ńĎŠĽông tŠļ°i cŠĽēng 3111 vŠĽõi trŠļ°ng th√°i kŠļŅt nŠĽĎi th√†nh c√īng (connected).","H√†m mem::compress gŠļ∑p lŠĽói 77 lŠļßn tr√™n tŠĽēng sŠĽĎ 149 lŠļßn gŠĽći, tŠĽ∑ lŠĽá thŠļ•t bŠļ°i khoŠļ£ng 51.6%.","ńźŠĽô trŠĽÖ trung b√¨nh cŠĽßa h√†m mem::compress rŠļ•t cao, l√™n tŠĽõi 66372.03 ms (khoŠļ£ng 66.4 gi√Ęy).","KŠļŅt nŠĽĎi c∆° sŠĽü dŠĽĮ liŠĽáu Key-Value (kvConnectivity) ŠĽēn ńĎŠĽčnh vŠĽõi ńĎŠĽô trŠĽÖ rŠļ•t thŠļ•p chŠĽČ 2.67 ms.","HŠĽá thŠĽĎng tŠĽĪ ngŠļĮt (circuitBreaker) hiŠĽán ńĎang ŠĽü trŠļ°ng th√°i ńĎ√≥ng (closed) v√† kh√īng c√≥ cŠļ£nh b√°o (alerts) n√†o ńĎ∆įŠĽ£c k√≠ch hoŠļ°t."],"files":["/Users/zasuo/Library/Application Support/rtk/tee/1779357843_curl.log"],"id":"obs_mpfbpuvu_0806c338213f","importance":4,"narrative":"LŠĽánh kiŠĽÉm tra sŠĽ©c khŠĽŹe dŠĽčch vŠĽ• AgentMemory ńĎ∆įŠĽ£c thŠĽĪc hiŠĽán nhŠļĪm thu thŠļ≠p dŠĽĮ liŠĽáu vŠļ≠n h√†nh thŠĽĪc tŠļŅ cŠĽßa hŠĽá thŠĽĎng l∆įu trŠĽĮ th√īng tin. KŠļŅt quŠļ£ cho thŠļ•y mŠļ∑c d√Ļ hŠļ° tŠļßng kŠļŅt nŠĽĎi Key-Value hoŠļ°t ńĎŠĽông tŠĽĎt, tiŠļŅn tr√¨nh n√©n bŠĽô nhŠĽõ (mem::compress) ńĎang gŠļ∑p sŠĽĪ cŠĽĎ nghi√™m trŠĽćng vŠĽĀ hiŠĽáu nńÉng vŠĽõi ńĎŠĽô trŠĽÖ cŠĽĪc cao v√† tŠĽ∑ lŠĽá lŠĽói lŠĽõn. ńźiŠĽĀu n√†y cŠļ£nh b√°o vŠĽĀ mŠĽôt ńĎiŠĽÉm nghŠļĹn hŠĽá thŠĽĎng cŠļßn ńĎ∆įŠĽ£c xŠĽ≠ l√Ĺ ńĎŠĽÉ tr√°nh l√†m giŠļ£m trŠļ£i nghiŠĽám l∆įu trŠĽĮ l√Ęu d√†i cŠĽßa AI agent.","sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","subtitle":"ChŠļ°y lŠĽánh curl qua rtk ńĎŠĽÉ lŠļ•y th√īng tin sŠĽ©c khŠĽŹe hŠĽá thŠĽĎng","timestamp":"2026-05-21T10:04:03.317Z","title":"KiŠĽÉm tra trŠļ°ng th√°i hoŠļ°t ńĎŠĽông cŠĽßa dŠĽčch vŠĽ• AgentMemory","type":"command_run"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mpfbpuvy_193d2467eeaf":{"observation":{"concepts":["vector index dimension mismatch","EACCES permission denied","Xenova transformers cache","AgentMemory startup telemetry"],"confidence":1,"facts":["The persisted vector index was discarded due to dimension mismatch (disk: 2048 vs active: 384) while AGENTMEMORY_DROP_STALE_INDEX=true was set.","AgentMemory viewer successfully started on http://localhost:3114 (fallback from 3113).","An EACCES permission denied error occurred when writing to the Xenova transformers cache directory at /opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/@agentmemory/agentmemory/node_modules/@xenova/transformers/.cache.","The system connected to OTel engine at ws://localhost:49134/otel and registered a worker."],"files":["/Users/zasuo/.agentmemory/server.log"],"id":"obs_mpfbpuvy_193d2467eeaf","importance":6,"narrative":"Tailing the AgentMemory server log revealed critical startup events and errors. First, the persisted vector index had incompatible dimensions and was discarded automatically to prevent errors. Second, a permission denied (EACCES) error prevents the Xenova transformers library from creating its cache directory under the global Homebrew node_modules, which blocks local model initialization.","sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","subtitle":"Inspection of server.log reveals vector dimension mismatch and permission issues","timestamp":"2026-05-21T10:04:03.320Z","title":"AgentMemory server logs show index drop and EACCES cache directory error","type":"error"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mpfbpuyh_15d6cc9aac67":{"observation":{"concepts":["AgentMemory","knowledge graph extraction","memory consolidation","agent memory compression"],"confidence":1,"facts":["AgentMemory v0.9.21 is connected, healthy, and running on http://localhost:3111.","Current session has 1 active session, 0 observations, 0 memories, and 0 graph nodes/edges.","Heap usage is 31 MB and uptime is 30 seconds.","Key features enabled: GRAPH_EXTRACTION_ENABLED, CONSOLIDATION_ENABLED, AGENTMEMORY_AUTO_COMPRESS, and AGENTMEMORY_INJECT_CONTEXT."],"files":[],"id":"obs_mpfbpuyh_15d6cc9aac67","importance":3,"narrative":"The agent verified the status and configuration of the AgentMemory service using the 'rtk agentmemory status' command. The service is healthy and all key memory features, including consolidation and knowledge graph extraction, are fully active for the current session.","sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","subtitle":"AgentMemory is connected and healthy at http://localhost:3111","timestamp":"2026-05-21T10:04:03.416Z","title":"Check AgentMemory status and active features","type":"command_run"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mpfbq7pd_34d5db93d098":{"observation":{"concepts":["npm package configuration","browser bundles","transformers.js"],"confidence":1,"facts":["The @xenova/transformers package version is 2.17.2.","Dependencies are onnxruntime-web (1.14.0), sharp (^0.32.0), and @huggingface/jinja (^0.2.2).","The optional dependency is onnxruntime-node (1.14.0).","Browser configuration disables fs, path, url, sharp, and onnxruntime-node.","The package main entry point is ./src/transformers.js and ESM type is module."],"files":["/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/@agentmemory/agentmemory/node_modules/@xenova/transformers/package.json"],"id":"obs_mpfbq7pd_34d5db93d098","importance":2,"narrative":"The agent inspected the package.json of @xenova/transformers to analyze its build scripts, entry points, and dependency constraints. This information is valuable to understand how the transformers library operates within the node_modules of @agentmemory. The findings confirm that specific native modules like sharp and onnxruntime-node are disabled in the browser bundle configuration.","sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","subtitle":"Inspected the package metadata and dependencies of @xenova/transformers inside @agentmemory","timestamp":"2026-05-21T10:04:19.934Z","title":"Read @xenova/transformers package.json configuration","type":"file_read"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mpfbrdio_e3b213cdbfaf":{"observation":{"concepts":["Node preloading","Xenova transformers cache","agentmemory server configuration","Node.js --import option"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Added resolve_xenova_transformers_main to locate global npm @xenova/transformers main file.","Created install_xenova_cache_preload to generate xenova-cache.mjs preloading cache settings.","Updated start_agentmemory_server to inject the preload script via Node --import option in NODE_OPTIONS.","The patch was applied successfully to setup.sh with exit code 0."],"files":["setup.sh"],"id":"obs_mpfbrdio_e3b213cdbfaf","importance":6,"narrative":"The patch updates setup.sh to configure a preload script for @xenova/transformers within agentmemory. By generating xenova-cache.mjs and importing it using the Node --import flag via NODE_OPTIONS, it ensures the transformers library uses the specified local cache directory instead of default paths. This resolves cache issues for local embeddings during agentmemory server startup.","sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","subtitle":"Integrate preload script configuring transformers cache via Node import option","timestamp":"2026-05-21T10:05:14.127Z","title":"Configure Xenova transformers cache preload in AgentMemory setup","type":"file_edit"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mpfbrn4c_30afeca4a7a8":{"observation":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpfbrn4c_30afeca4a7a8","raw":{"tool_input":{"command":"rtk bash -n setup.sh"},"tool_name":"Bash","tool_output":""},"sessionId":"019e49d8-e7a0-71d1-a19e-64b2b9af690e","timestamp":"2026-05-21T10:05:26.569Z","toolInput":{"command":"rtk bash -n setup.sh"},"toolName":"Bash"},"type":"raw"},"obs_mpfbrn4j_e18a64e331af":{"observation":{"hookType":"post_tool_use","id":"obs_mpfbrn4j_e18a64e331af","raw":{"tool_input":{"command":"rtk git diff -- setup.sh"},"tool_name":"Bash","tool_output":"setup.sh | 559 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------\n 1 file changed, 508 insertions(+), 51 deletions(-)\n\n--- Changes ---\n\nsetup.sh\n  @@ -1,27 +1,23 @@\n  -# Configures AgentMemory for Antigravity, Codex CLI, and Claude Code.\n  +# Owns agy-local proxy setup and delegates AgentMemory/Codex/Claude wiring to upstream CLIs.\n   \n   set -euo pipefail\n   \n  +SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")\" && pwd)\"\n  +AGENTMEMORY_ENV=\"${HOME}/.agentmemory/.env\"\n  +AGENTMEMORY_DIR=\"${HOME}/.agentmemory\"\n  +AGY_BIN=\"${HOME}/.local/bin/agy\"\n  +AGY_PORT=3129\n   CLIENT=\"all\"\n  -SKIP_UPSTREAM=false\n  -while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n  -  case \"$1\" in\n  -    --client=*) CLIENT=\"${1#*=}\"; shift ;;\n  -    --client) CLIENT=\"${2:-all}\"; shift 2 ;;\n  -    --skip-upstream) SKIP_UPSTREAM=true; shift ;;\n  -    antigravity|codex|claude-code|all) CLIENT=\"$1\"; shift ;;\n  -    *) warn \"BŠĽŹ qua argument kh√īng hŠĽó trŠĽ£: $1\"; shift ;;\n  -  esac\n  -done\n  +DROP_STALE_INDEX=false\n  +CLEAR_DATA=false\n  +SKIP_CONNECT=false\n  +SKIP_DOCTOR=false\n  +TRANSFORMERS_CACHE=\"${HOME}/.cache/xenova-transformers\"\n   \n  -RED='\\033[0;31m'\n  -GREEN='\\033[0;32m'\n  -YELLOW='\\033[1;33m'\n  -CYAN='\\033[0;36m'\n  -BOLD='\\033[1m'\n  -NC='\\033[0m'\n  +RED='\\033[0;31m'; GREEN='\\033[0;32m'; YELLOW='\\033[1;33m'\n  +CYAN='\\033[0;36m'; BOLD='\\033[1m'; NC='\\033[0m'\n   \n   info() { echo -e \"${CYAN}[INFO]${NC} $*\"; }\n   ok()   { echo -e \"${GREEN}[OK]${NC}   $*\"; }\n  @@ -29,46 +25,502 @@ warn() { echo -e \"${YELLOW}[WARN]${NC} $*\"; }\n  -SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")\" && pwd)\"\n  +usage() {\n  +  cat <<'USAGE'\n  +Usage: bash setup.sh [options]\n  +\n  +Options:\n  +  --client <all|antigravity|codex|claude-code>\n  +  --agy-bin <path>\n  +  --port <number>\n  +  --drop-stale-index\n  +  --clear-data\n  +  --skip-connect\n  +  --skip-doctor\n  +  -h, --help\n  +USAGE\n  +}\n  +\n  +while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n  +  case \"$1\" in\n  +    --client=*) CLIENT=\"${1#*=}\"; shift ;;\n  +    --client) [[ $# -ge 2 ]] || err \"--client requires a value\"; CLIENT=\"$2\"; shift 2 ;;\n  +    --agy-bin=*) AGY_BIN=\"${1#*=}\"; shift ;;\n  +    --agy-bin) [[ $# -ge 2 ]] || err \"--agy-bin requires a value\"; AGY_BIN=\"$2\"; shift 2 ;;\n  +    --port=*) AGY_PORT=\"${1#*=}\"; shift ;;\n  +    --port) [[ $# -ge 2 ]] || err \"--port requires a value\"; AGY_PORT=\"$2\"; shift 2 ;;\n  +    --drop-stale-index) DROP_STALE_INDEX=true; shift ;;\n  +    --clear-data) CLEAR_DATA=true; shift ;;\n  +    --skip-connect) SKIP_CONNECT=true; shift ;;\n  +    --skip-doctor) SKIP_DOCTOR=true; shift ;;\n  +    -h|--help) usage; exit 0 ;;\n  +    *) err \"Unsupported argument: $1\" ;;\n  +  esac\n  +done\n  +\n  +case \"$CLIENT\" in\n  +  all|antigravity|codex|claude-code) ;;\n  +  *) err \"--client must be one of: all, antigravity, codex, claude-code\" ;;\n  +esac\n  +\n  +case \"$AGY_PORT\" in\n  +  ''|*[!0-9]*) err \"--port must be a number\" ;;\n  +esac\n  +\n  +has_client() {\n  +  [[ \"$CLIENT\" == \"all\" || \"$CLIENT\" == \"$1\" ]]\n  +}\n  +\n  +require_command() {\n  +  command -v \"$1\" >/dev/null 2>&1 || err \"$1 not found\"\n  +}\n  +\n  +upsert_env() {\n  +  local key=\"$1\" value=\"$2\" file=\"$3\"\n  +  mkdir -p \"$(dirname \"$file\")\"\n  +  if [[ -f \"$file\" ]] && grep -qE \"^#?[[:space:]]*${key}[[:space:]]*=\" \"$file\"; then\n  +    sed -i '' \"s|^#*[[:space:]]*${key}[[:space:]]*=.*|${key}=${value}|\" \"$file\"\n  +  else\n  +    echo \"${key}=${value}\" >> \"$file\"\n  +  fi\n  +}\n  +\n  +backup_data() {\n  +  step \"Backup AgentMemory data\"\n  +  local ts backup_dir copied=false\n  +  ts=\"$(date -u +\"%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ\")\"\n  +  backup_dir=\"${AGENTMEMORY_DIR}/backups/setup-${ts}\"\n  +  mkdir -p \"$backup_dir\"\n  +\n  +  if [[ -f \"$AGENTMEMORY_ENV\" ]]; then cp \"$AGENTMEMORY_ENV\" \"${backup_dir}/env\"; copied=true; fi\n  +  if [[ -f \"${AGENTMEMORY_DIR}/standalone.json\" ]]; then cp \"${AGENTMEMORY_DIR}/standalone.json\" \"$backup_dir/\"; copied=true; fi\n  +  if [[ -d \"${SCRIPT_DIR}/data\" ]]; then cp -R \"${SCRIPT_DIR}/data\" \"${backup_dir}/data\"; copied=true; fi\n  +\n  +  [[ \"$copied\" == \"true\" ]] && ok \"Backup: ${backup_dir}\" || { rmdir \"$backup_dir\" 2>/dev/null || true; warn \"No AgentMemory data found to backup\"; }\n  +}\n   \n  -check_prereqs() {\n  -  step \"KiŠĽÉm tra prerequisites\"\n  -  command -v node >/dev/null 2>&1 || err \"Node.js >= 20 required. TŠļ£i: https://nodejs.org\"\n  -  command -v npm >/dev/null 2>&1 || err \"npm required\"\n  -  command -v npx >/dev/null 2>&1 || err \"npx required\"\n  +clear_data() {\n  +  backup_data\n  +  step \"Clear AgentMemory runtime data\"\n  +  agentmemory stop --force >/dev/null 2>&1 || true\n  +  if [[ -d \"${SCRIPT_DIR}/data\" ]]; then rm -rf \"${SCRIPT_DIR}/data\"; ok \"Removed ${SCRIPT_DIR}/data\"; fi\n  +  for f in standalone.json engine-state.json server.log engine.log agy-proxy.log; do\n  +    if [[ -e \"${AGENTMEMORY_DIR}/${f}\" ]]; then rm -f \"${AGENTMEMORY_DIR}/${f}\"; ok \"Removed ${AGENTMEMORY_DIR}/${f}\"; fi\n  +  done\n  +}\n  +\n  +patch_agentmemory_env() {\n  +  step \"Patch ~/.agentmemory/.env for agy-local\"\n  +  mkdir -p \"$AGENTMEMORY_DIR\" \"$TRANSFORMERS_CACHE\"\n   \n  -  node -e \"process.exit(parseInt(process.versions.node) < 20 ? 1 : 0)\" || \\\n  -    err \"Node.js >= 20 required (hiŠĽán tŠļ°i: $(node --version))\"\n  +  upsert_env \"AGENTMEMORY_URL\" \"http://localhost:3111\" \"$AGENTMEMORY_ENV\"\n  +  upsert_env \"EMBEDDING_PROVIDER\" \"local\" \"$AGENTMEMORY_ENV\"\n  +  upsert_env \"TRANSFORMERS_CACHE\" \"$TRANSFORMERS_CACHE\" \"$AGENTMEMORY_ENV\"\n  +  upsert_env \"OPENAI_API_KEY\" \"dummy\" \"$AGENTMEMORY_ENV\"\n  ... (408 lines truncated)\n  @@ -76,19 +528,24 @@ main() {\n  -  check_prereqs\n  -  build_cli\n  -  run_setup\n  +  check_prerequisites\n  +  build_proxy\n  +  agentmemory init || warn \"agentmemory init skipped or reported existing config\"\n  +  [[ \"$CLEAR_DATA\" == \"true\" ]] && clear_data\n  +  patch_agentmemory_env\n  +  start_agy_proxy\n  +  setup_clients\n  +  start_agentmemory_server\n  +  run_doctor\n     verify_setup\n   \n     echo \"\"\n  -  echo -e \"${GREEN}${BOLD}‚úď Setup ho√†n tŠļ•t.${NC}\"\n  +  echo -e \"${GREEN}${BOLD}‚úď Setup complete.${NC}\"\n     echo -e \"  Client       : ${CLIENT}\"\n  -  echo -e \"  Env          : ~/.agentmemory/.env\"\n  -  echo -e \"  Upstream     : ${SCRIPT_DIR}/agentmemory ${CYAN}(no .git)${NC}\"\n  -  echo -e \"  Embeddings   : local all-MiniLM-